@EU_Commission EU behind the times as usual. 

Most new phones are/ will be wireless for charging and Bluetooth for accessories. 

Pointless legislation far too late.

@EU_Commission Politicians thinking they are helping...

I'm not against a common charger, but why enforcing it?

Do you guys actually know how much electronic waste exists with USB-C chargers? It's 3W? 9W? 15W? 45W?

@EU_Commission [THREAD] I totally agree but as someone that change country often I propose some extra steps:
1- Extend this rule to as much electric device as possible (toothbrush, shaver, e-book reader, smartwatch...)
2- The device should have a usb-c (female) port and not an attached cable
